         <div type="commentary">
         <p>B+B states “The inscriptions, which shows some Sanskrit nominatives, and ends with two Prakrit words, seems to record merely the name of some Brahmans who visited the caves". This interpretation would put this inscription in line with the later Pahlavi inscriptions at the site (KI00104 - KI00106).</p>
         <p n="7-8"><foreign>bohoI</foreign>. It is tempting to compare this with Pkt. <foreign>pahuvaï</foreign>, "to reach". The Socotra graffiti commonly end with a variation of the Skt. p.p.  <foreign>prāpta</foreign> (see Strauch 2012: 282 for examples).</p>
         </div>
          
          
          
          
